      "id": "1773254212907-fse0tqhvf",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I have a few questions before I start making changes:\n\n1. **About door placement** - Right now in your game, the stairs to the next level are already in a separate room from the locked doors. Locked doors only block bonus treasure rooms. Do you want to keep it that way, or change something about how stairs and doors relate?\n\n2. **About the key store** - You mentioned players should be able to buy keys in a store. Your game already has a shop on each floor that sells weapons, potions, etc. Should I add keys to that existing shop, or create a whole new separate key shop?\n\n3. **What should be behind locked doors?** - Currently locked rooms have better weapons and armor. Do you want to add anything extra special behind those doors, like unique items you can't find anywhere else?\n\nLet me know your thoughts on these and I'll get started right away!",
      "isShownToUser": true,
      "timestamp": 1773254220330,
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {}
    },
