      "id": "1773254541103-rzwpa66az",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Now let me ensure stairs are never placed in vault rooms. Looking at the dungeon generation, stairs are placed in the **last room** (`rooms[rooms.length - 1]`), and vaults are picked from `rooms[1..rooms.length-2]` (index range `randInt(1, rooms.length - 2)`). This means the last room is already excluded from being a vault. However, I should add an extra safeguard. Let me verify the vault index selection and add protection:",
      "isShownToUser": true,
      "timestamp": 1773254549003,
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "1773254549005-fuqkmbq9w",
