      "metadata": {
        "toolName": "Read"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "1773254549006-lcnnljvdi",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The vault index is `randInt(1, rooms.length - 2)`, which means it picks from the 2nd room to the 2nd-to-last room. Stairs are placed in `rooms[rooms.length - 1]` (the last room) and `rooms[0]` is where the player spawns. So stairs are already never in a vault room. But let me add a comment to make this explicit, and also add a safeguard in the stairs placement to skip vault rooms:",
      "isShownToUser": true,
      "timestamp": 1773254565687,
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {}
