      "content": "Everything's done and building. Here's what I added:\n\n**6 New Environmental Monsters:**\n\n- **Fire Elemental** (floor 5+) — Spreads pools of **fire/lava** around you when it attacks. Enemies standing on lava deal +20-40% extra damage, so watch your positioning!\n- **Storm Wisp** (floor 4+) — Fast and creates pools of **electrified water** around you. Electric weapon attacks deal 2x damage on water tiles.\n- **Poison Spitter** (floor 3+) — Leaves **toxic pools** where it strikes. Standing on poison boosts poison weapon damage by 40%.\n- **Frost Wraith** (floor 5+) — Coats the ground in **ice** around you. Enemies on ice take 20% more damage.\n- **Shadow Stalker** (floor 6+) — Fast and deadly, creates patches of **shadow** wherever it hits. Attacks from shadow tiles deal 30% more damage.\n- **Mud Crawler** (floor 4+) — Tough and tanky, spreads **mud** that slows everyone down and makes them easier to hit.\n\n**How Environmental Attacks Work:**\n- Each time one of these monsters hits you, there's a chance (40-55% depending on the monster) it creates 2-4 terrain tiles in a small area around you\n- The terrain is permanent for that floor — it changes the battlefield as the fight goes on\n- This works both ways! If you position carefully, you can use the terrain the monsters create against them (e.g. lure monsters onto their own ice patches to take extra damage)\n\n**Boss Support:**\nBosses can now also use terrain attacks as special abilities, flooding larger areas with environmental hazards. This opens up future boss designs that reshape the battlefield.",
